<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,685,1072]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,973,999]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Comments:</emphasis>
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3014903384" collectorName="Virgil von Helmreichen" country="Brazil" location="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Rio de Janeiro" typeStatus="lectotype">
The 
<typeStatus box="[395,498,973,999]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a metander specimen possibly collected by the Austrian mine engineer 
<collectorName pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Virgil von Helmreichen</collectorName>
zu Brunnfeld (1805–1852) during a trip between 
<collectingRegion box="[875,1042,1009,1035]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
(
<collectingCountry box="[1059,1130,1009,1036]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) and Asunción (
<collectingCountry box="[1321,1429,1009,1035]" name="Paraguay" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Otruba, G." box="[159,305,1045,1072]" pageId="6" pageNumber="237" refId="ref22759" refString="Otruba, G. (1969) Helmreichen von Brunnfeld, Virgil. Neue Deutsche Biographie (NDB). Duncker &amp; Humblot, Berlim, 504 pp." type="book" year="1969">Otruba 1969</bibRefCitation>
). The type locality cannot be further narrowed down than to 
<collectingCountry box="[985,1057,1045,1071]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="237">Brazil</collectingCountry>
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
